02:58.720 --> 03:00.889
♪ To Grandmother's house we go ♪

03:00.972 --> 03:03.057
♪ The horse knows the way
To carry the sleigh ♪

03:03.141 --> 03:05.310
♪ Through white and drifted snow ♪

03:05.393 --> 03:08.938
♪ Over the river and through the woods
Oh, how the wind does blow ♪

03:09.022 --> 03:13.318
♪ It stings the toes and bites the nose
As over the ground we go, hooray! ♪

03:13.401 --> 03:14.736
Perfect.

03:14.819 --> 03:16.821
I wish I had me as a wife.

03:17.655 --> 03:19.908
-Ugh! Jesus!
-[grunts]

03:19.991 --> 03:22.160
Stop messing with my evil eye!

03:22.243 --> 03:24.037
-Stop resisting arrest!
-Ah!

03:24.120 --> 03:26.414
-[Bill grunts]
-Goddamn it to hell!

03:27.916 --> 03:30.001
I'm sorry, kids.

03:30.084 --> 03:33.630
This Thanksgiving
is a very important one for me.

03:33.713 --> 03:37.175
I just need you to stay out of my hair
while I get everything ready.

03:37.258 --> 03:39.928
If you can't sit still,
then please do me a favor

03:40.011 --> 03:41.512
and annoy your dad instead.

03:41.596 --> 03:44.182
He's taking his morning beer nap.

03:44.265 --> 03:45.934
[upbeat music playing on TV]

03:46.017 --> 03:47.435
[announcer] Tonight, after football,

03:47.518 --> 03:50.480
it's the ABS Thanksgiving Special,

03:50.563 --> 03:53.650
with the stars of Colt Luger,

03:53.733 --> 03:54.984
Bruce Again!,

03:55.068 --> 03:56.110
Police Cop!,

03:56.194 --> 03:57.820
Beach Magician M.D.!,

03:57.904 --> 03:59.822
My Dog, The President!,

03:59.906 --> 04:04.410
and Secretary of Agriculture, Earl Butz!

04:04.494 --> 04:06.537
Frank? Frank?

04:06.621 --> 04:09.249
[announcer] And it all ends
with the return of stunt legend

04:09.332 --> 04:11.668
Buster Thunder Junior!

04:11.751 --> 04:14.420
This doctor said I'd never punch again!

04:14.504 --> 04:15.421
[grunts]

04:15.505 --> 04:17.548
Who's the doctor now?

04:17.632 --> 04:19.217
Yeehaw!

04:19.300 --> 04:20.885
Frank, are you asleep?

04:20.969 --> 04:22.929
[snoring]

04:25.515 --> 04:27.850
-I'm pregnant again.
-The fuck you are!

04:27.934 --> 04:31.271
Look at this mess. The house has
to look immaculate when my parents come,

04:31.354 --> 04:32.897
like nobody lives here.

04:32.981 --> 04:36.442
Honey, take it easy.
Don't put so much pressure on yourself.

04:36.526 --> 04:39.904
I have to. I'm really worried about today.

04:39.988 --> 04:42.699
It took so much to get my dad and Louis
in the same room,

04:42.782 --> 04:45.868
and if it doesn't go right,
we'll never have the chance again.

04:45.952 --> 04:49.163
Oh, I understand, honey.
I'll do anything to help you.

04:49.247 --> 04:51.040
Could you take the baby
and make a quick run to the store

04:51.124 --> 04:52.208
to get cranberry sauce?

04:52.292 --> 04:55.003
Aw, Jesus, Sue,
the store's gonna be a zoo!

04:55.086 --> 04:58.840
Whatever we're missing, I'm sure you made
plenty of other bullshit for us to eat.

04:58.923 --> 05:01.342
Bill and Maureen
ruined the cranberries my dad loves!

05:01.426 --> 05:03.428
Well, your dad ruins everything I love.

05:04.095 --> 05:05.513
Please?

05:06.806 --> 05:07.890
Ugh.

05:07.974 --> 05:09.058
Okay.

05:09.142 --> 05:10.268
I'll go get them.

05:10.351 --> 05:12.312
Your punishment for fucking up

05:12.395 --> 05:14.439
is spending quality time
with your old man.

05:14.522 --> 05:16.357
-Aw! No fair!
-No fair!

05:17.025 --> 05:19.444
Some fucking holiday this is.

05:19.527 --> 05:22.905
Got to take my dad's car
because the safety seat's in it.

05:22.989 --> 05:24.991
I guess we're coddling babies now.

05:25.074 --> 05:29.245
Goddamn seat, why won't this...
why won't this stupid thing tighten?

05:29.329 --> 05:31.164
[gasping]

05:31.247 --> 05:32.290
Holy shit!

05:33.333 --> 05:35.209
Uh, I don't think we need
to tell Mom about that.

05:35.293 --> 05:36.669
What's in it for me?

05:36.753 --> 05:39.172
-Well, do you like Christmas?
-Yeah.

05:39.255 --> 05:42.216
-Would you like to live see another one?
-Yeah.

05:42.300 --> 05:45.511
Then shut the fuck up
and help me with this baby seat!

05:45.595 --> 05:48.389
-[line ringing]
-Come on, Alice, pick up.

05:49.390 --> 05:52.727
[Dr. Goldman on recording]
♪ No one's home, please leave a message ♪

05:52.810 --> 05:56.314
♪ For the Goldmans at the tone ♪

05:56.397 --> 05:57.440
[beep]

05:57.523 --> 06:01.027
Alice, hey, this is Kevin Murphy from...

06:01.110 --> 06:02.737
your boyfriend.

06:03.613 --> 06:05.782
Are you there? Please pick up.

06:05.865 --> 06:09.243
I'm really sorry about the other night
when you got all weird. I just know that--

06:09.327 --> 06:10.870
-[Sue] Kevin?
-Alice! I love you.

06:10.953 --> 06:12.789
I know you're mad,
but everything'll be okay

06:12.872 --> 06:14.332
if we do the kiss-kiss game
with your boobies.

06:14.415 --> 06:16.459
-[Sue] It's your mother.
-Oh God!

06:16.542 --> 06:20.004
What are you doing at Alice's house?
Are you talking about me?

06:20.088 --> 06:21.839
[Sue] Get off the phone
so I can call the neighbors

06:21.923 --> 06:23.925
to tell them what time to come over
for coffee and cake.

06:24.008 --> 06:25.343
Mom, you sound like a lunatic!

06:25.426 --> 06:27.637
Would you put Alice on the phone?

06:27.720 --> 06:29.722
Mom? Mom?

06:30.306 --> 06:31.224
Erwin?

06:31.307 --> 06:34.018
Off the fucking phone!

06:34.727 --> 06:36.145
What'd the phone ever do to you?

06:36.229 --> 06:40.316
Ah! You crumpled the bed!
I need to put coats on it later!

06:40.400 --> 06:44.320
Oh, I'm sorry I'm affected by gravity!
What do you want me to do?

06:46.197 --> 06:47.907
This sucks ass.

06:47.990 --> 06:50.243
I had a whole day of sulking planned.

06:50.326 --> 06:52.829
Then just a pinch-a the cinnamon.

06:52.912 --> 06:56.416
That's the secret
to a traditional Thanksgiving

06:56.499 --> 06:59.502
Tagliatelle Arrogost Bachagaloop!

06:59.585 --> 07:00.628
[doorbell rings]

07:01.504 --> 07:03.464
-[chuckles] Hey, my man!
-[baby babbling]

07:03.548 --> 07:06.300
I'm... I'm going to say Petey?
Is your mom home?

07:06.384 --> 07:10.680
She's busy at the moment.
You don't look like you usually do.

07:10.763 --> 07:13.641
I can't see the pulse in your eyes.

07:13.724 --> 07:17.353
Well, that's 'cause I stopped taking
the, uh... special vitamins

07:17.437 --> 07:18.521
that kept me perky.

07:18.604 --> 07:21.858
You mean Schedule II narcotics?

07:21.941 --> 07:22.942
Yeah.

07:23.025 --> 07:25.027
[baby crying]

07:26.362 --> 07:29.490
All right, little man.
Can you be cool for just a little while?

07:29.574 --> 07:31.909
You're giving Daddy the sweats.
[chuckles nervously]

07:33.244 --> 07:35.079
Listen, Petey, I got a problem.

07:35.163 --> 07:37.123
I'm stuck raising my little man by myself

07:37.206 --> 07:39.667
because, uh, his mom
ran off with a Santa elf,

07:39.750 --> 07:43.463
so could I ask your mom
how to get a fussy baby to eat?

07:43.546 --> 07:46.424
Oh, she's never had trouble with that.

07:46.507 --> 07:48.759
[Anthony] Nom, nom.
You know what? You know what?

07:48.843 --> 07:50.261
Nom, nom, nom, nom.

07:50.344 --> 07:52.430
You know what? You know what?

07:52.513 --> 07:53.556
-Aw.
-You know what?

07:53.639 --> 07:56.517
You've got a big Thanksgiving appetite.

07:56.601 --> 07:59.103
I can feel your tonsils getting swollen.

07:59.187 --> 08:03.649
I went to Tijuana once
and paid 30 pesos to see that.

08:03.733 --> 08:04.775
Never again.

08:06.861 --> 08:11.532
Aw, I don't get why we all have
to clear out so Mom can be crazy.

08:11.616 --> 08:14.994
Ah, she's not crazy. [splutters]
She's just doing crazy things. Okay?

08:15.077 --> 08:16.329
This is important to her.

08:16.412 --> 08:18.831
So you have to help her out
by minding your manners,

08:18.915 --> 08:21.334
getting your head out of your ass
about your girlfriend,

08:21.417 --> 08:24.253
and don't get upset if she says
Pop-Pop is dying of a brain tumor.

08:24.337 --> 08:25.505
Pop-Pop is dying?

08:25.588 --> 08:27.590
No, but Uncle Louis thinks he is.

08:27.673 --> 08:28.799
Why does he think that?

08:28.883 --> 08:30.468
Oh, because Mom told him he was.

08:30.551 --> 08:31.844
Why did she tell him that?

08:31.928 --> 08:35.598
Because she's crazy! People do
weird things when they love someone.

08:35.681 --> 08:39.227
[scoffs] Like you crying over
Grandpa Bill's box with the 91 on it?

08:39.310 --> 08:41.687
I still say it's probably a 16,

08:41.771 --> 08:43.648
and it might mean something!

08:43.731 --> 08:44.732
Shit!

08:44.815 --> 08:46.275
-[tires squeal]
-[kids scream]

08:46.359 --> 08:47.693
What the hell is this?

08:47.777 --> 08:49.904
I guess the parade is still going on.

08:49.987 --> 08:51.781
Oh, fucking Thanksgiving!

08:51.864 --> 08:54.158
Just go home and eat, you assholes!

08:54.242 --> 08:57.078
-[marching band playing]
-Come to Skinneees!

08:57.161 --> 09:00.164
You won't be horrified,
or your money back!

09:01.749 --> 09:05.169
-Where's the rest of the chicken?
-In the trash where it belongs!

09:06.462 --> 09:08.172
Ooh, a Tollway Turkey!

09:08.256 --> 09:09.590
Everybody gets a turkey!

09:09.674 --> 09:13.553
-[woman] Thanks, Mr. Mayor! We love you!
-Hey! Stop stealing my business!

09:13.636 --> 09:16.514
I should be filling those mouths!

09:16.597 --> 09:18.849
-[grunts]
-[squeals] Ow!

09:18.933 --> 09:20.643
Right in the implant!

09:20.726 --> 09:23.145
Nobody hits my girls but me!

09:23.229 --> 09:25.982
Keep your dirty birds to yourself!

09:26.065 --> 09:30.194
Fuck you!
I will turkey your grandchildren!

09:30.653 --> 09:31.862
[grunts]

09:34.907 --> 09:38.160
-[crowd screaming]
-No! No!

09:38.244 --> 09:40.871
My three-week-old dream!

09:42.540 --> 09:45.084
-There. Perfect.
-[dog whining]

09:45.167 --> 09:46.377
[gagging]

09:46.460 --> 09:48.045
Oh, shit!

09:48.129 --> 09:50.047
Major, no! Major!

09:50.131 --> 09:52.675
Hold it in! Hold it in!
Hold it in, sweet baby!

09:53.175 --> 09:54.552
Hello, angel.

09:56.262 --> 09:59.015
Well, this is a good omen.

09:59.098 --> 10:02.602
Hi, Mom. Hi, Dad. Uh, sorry about the...

10:04.270 --> 10:06.105
Never mind. Come in!

10:07.398 --> 10:10.234
So, where's that husband of yours?

10:10.318 --> 10:13.279
He get a new job
at the disappointment factory?

10:13.362 --> 10:17.325
No, he took the kids to the grocery store
to get the special cranberries you like.

10:17.408 --> 10:18.701
[grunts]

10:18.784 --> 10:21.746
Uh, speaking of special fruit
that's been in the can...

10:21.829 --> 10:26.125
Now, Stan, you promised
you'd be nice to Louis.

10:26.208 --> 10:29.420
He's making an effort to come here today.

10:29.503 --> 10:32.590
Fine, but if he gives me any lip,

10:32.673 --> 10:37.053
we have backup reservations
at the Szechuan Palace.

10:37.136 --> 10:39.430
They do a fantastic white rice.

10:39.513 --> 10:42.183
There's absolutely no taste!

10:42.266 --> 10:45.311
-[siren blares]
-[horn honks]

10:45.394 --> 10:48.648
...58, 59, 60,

10:48.731 --> 10:51.525
61, 62...

10:51.609 --> 10:54.111
Wait, that's a toenail! Give it back!

10:54.195 --> 10:57.073
Hey, lady, can you hurry up?
I got my baby in the car.

10:57.156 --> 10:59.367
Well, I got places to be too, you know.

10:59.450 --> 11:02.328
Aw, bullshit! You're buying cat food
on Thanksgiving.

11:03.496 --> 11:04.497
[baby babbling]

11:04.580 --> 11:08.167
-Hey, happy Turkey Day, Gooms!
-Uh, hey-a, Vic. What, uh...

11:08.250 --> 11:09.794
What are you doing here?

11:09.877 --> 11:14.340
Worried about what wild animal left
that surprise on your walkway last night?

11:14.423 --> 11:17.551
No, man, from the looks of that poop,
he's not gonna be around much longer.

11:17.635 --> 11:20.304
Something eating him alive
from the inside, know what I mean?

11:20.388 --> 11:23.182
-It's like a goddamn alien in there.
-[baby crying]

11:23.265 --> 11:27.019
Say, I need some advice
on how to calm down Vic Junior here.

11:27.103 --> 11:28.354
You guys have kids, right?

11:28.437 --> 11:30.523
-[groans]
-Uh...

11:30.606 --> 11:32.858
No, Vic, we don't.

11:32.942 --> 11:35.152
Uh, I'm afraid we can't help you.

11:35.236 --> 11:38.614
[crying]

11:38.698 --> 11:41.158
Aw, man, I don't know where else to turn.

11:41.242 --> 11:43.577
I knocked at Chet's place,
but he didn't answer.

11:43.661 --> 11:45.246
Let me try to soothe him.

11:45.329 --> 11:49.041
-Oh, it's okay, Evie. You don't have to.
-I already am!

11:49.125 --> 11:51.544
There you go. Evie's got you now.

11:51.627 --> 11:54.755
Oh, thank you. You two are good people.

11:54.839 --> 11:56.257
Uh...

11:56.340 --> 11:58.759
Yeah.

11:59.969 --> 12:02.722
In just four short hours,
Buster Thunder Junior

12:02.805 --> 12:06.517
will jump the Los Angeles River,
a majestic body of water

12:06.600 --> 12:09.854
that flows with the waste
of Hollywood's biggest stars.

12:09.937 --> 12:13.733
So, where's that brother of yours?

12:13.816 --> 12:16.152
Maybe he was arrested
at the bus station.

12:16.235 --> 12:17.570
-Again.
-Dad!

12:17.653 --> 12:21.782
Pardon me for acknowledging
the lavender elephant in the room.

12:21.866 --> 12:23.117
-[door opens]
-[Louis] Hi, Dad.

12:23.200 --> 12:24.201
[dramatic music plays]

12:24.285 --> 12:25.369
Louis.

12:25.453 --> 12:28.080
Oh, son, I hope you didn't hear

12:28.164 --> 12:32.126
the horrible thing
your father just said about you.

12:32.209 --> 12:33.294
I did.

12:34.920 --> 12:36.255
[dramatic music crescendos]

12:36.756 --> 12:37.673
Ah!

12:37.757 --> 12:38.758
I love you.

12:39.925 --> 12:41.469
And I forgive you.

12:41.552 --> 12:44.346
Well, this is, uh, quite the hello.

12:44.430 --> 12:48.893
I know I'm not supposed to say anything,
but you're so courageous.

12:48.976 --> 12:50.144
[Stan] Courageous?

12:50.227 --> 12:52.354
I'm not afraid of catching anything.

12:52.438 --> 12:54.398
Just don't touch
that scraped knuckle, okay?

12:54.482 --> 12:57.109
Oh, this is wonderful.

12:57.193 --> 12:59.653
Yeah, so great.
How about some mulled wine?

12:59.737 --> 13:02.114
I want us to get along, son.

13:02.198 --> 13:05.326
This has been eating
at the pit of my stomach.

13:05.409 --> 13:08.662
-It moved to your stomach?
-Hey, look, a deodorant commercial!

13:08.746 --> 13:11.040
-[women] ♪ That's Turteltaub's! ♪
-[men] ♪ And sons! ♪

13:11.123 --> 13:13.125
[man] It's a schmear for your pits!

13:13.626 --> 13:17.254
[humming "Hush, Little Baby"]

13:17.338 --> 13:19.840
Hey, you're a real natural there, Lady G.

13:19.924 --> 13:22.551
-I practice with the dog every night.
-[whimpering]

13:22.635 --> 13:24.804
[Goomer] Turns out dogs
don't need solid food.

13:24.887 --> 13:26.138
Very cool.

13:26.222 --> 13:29.099
So, uh, what'd you do
to get him to be so calm?

13:29.183 --> 13:32.228
If I told you that,
you'd never bring him back.

13:32.311 --> 13:34.480
[chuckles] Oh, yeah,
you're probably right.

13:34.563 --> 13:36.982
Well, I don't want to interfere
with your Thanksgiving. We should go.

13:37.066 --> 13:39.527
No. I'm not finished yet.

13:39.610 --> 13:42.530
But I promised the little guy I'd teach
him how to adjust a carburetor, so--

13:42.613 --> 13:44.490
-I said back off!
-[Goomer chuckles]

13:44.573 --> 13:46.408
Well, you heard her.

13:46.492 --> 13:49.161
Why don't you have a tall glass
of Goomer's special eggnog,

13:49.245 --> 13:52.331
and we'll catch up on neighborhood gossip
when you wake up?

13:55.835 --> 14:01.131
Oh, I never thought
a nightmare could smell so delicious.

14:01.215 --> 14:03.634
Robert, I came as soon as you called.

14:03.717 --> 14:07.638
I'm so sorry
about your unfortunate misfortune.

14:07.721 --> 14:10.558
Thank you, Lou. You're a good friend.

14:10.641 --> 14:14.728
And don't despair.
Your insurance will cover this.

14:14.812 --> 14:16.564
I don't have insurance.

14:16.647 --> 14:20.943
I spent the money on this chicken suit,
which I did insure.

14:21.652 --> 14:25.072
Then you should most definitely despair.

14:25.155 --> 14:26.740
That's why I called.

14:26.824 --> 14:31.287
Now that I'm ruined,
I won't be able to pay you what I owe you.

14:31.370 --> 14:33.038
I hate to disappoint you,

14:33.122 --> 14:37.084
but I'm afraid
we're gonna have to cancel our agreement.

14:37.167 --> 14:39.545
I hate to disappoint you,

14:39.628 --> 14:43.465
but as they say in Sicily, no backsies.

14:43.549 --> 14:45.175
-[Pogo] Oh.
-[dramatic music plays]

14:49.597 --> 14:51.765
Oh, boy, they're here.

14:51.849 --> 14:53.976
All right, kids,
get ready to watch a battle royale

14:54.059 --> 14:56.353
between the Sadist
and the San Francisco Treat.

14:56.437 --> 14:58.397
Why does Pop-Pop hate Uncle Louis?

14:58.480 --> 15:01.150
Sweetie, hate is such a strong word.

15:01.233 --> 15:05.863
All Pop-Pop has done for the last 15 years
is reject his own flesh and blood.

15:05.946 --> 15:07.823
Uncle Louis is a pickle sniffer.

15:07.907 --> 15:09.074
-Hey!
-Ow!

15:09.158 --> 15:12.328
He's not a pickle sniffer.
He's a song-and-dance man.

15:12.411 --> 15:13.662
And you shouldn't judge him.

15:13.746 --> 15:16.957
If what Uncle Louis does makes him happy,
then so be it.

15:17.041 --> 15:18.500
Live and let live.

15:18.584 --> 15:22.379
Now, having said that, if I ever catch you
playing footsie with another man,

15:22.463 --> 15:25.132
I swear to God,
I will put you through that fucking wall!

15:25.215 --> 15:28.010
Now get inside
and treat him like an equal!

15:29.470 --> 15:30.596
What the fuck?

15:30.679 --> 15:32.348
[Stan and Louis laughing]

15:32.431 --> 15:35.851
Stan. Louis. Happy Thanksgiving.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.269
Hello, Frank.

15:37.353 --> 15:41.190
What moldy, dented cans
did you get at the food bank this year?

15:41.273 --> 15:44.944
Yeah, and which one of your shoes
are we boiling for dinner?

15:45.027 --> 15:46.278
[both laugh]

15:46.362 --> 15:47.655
[Louis] He's so cheap!

15:47.738 --> 15:51.742
[Stan] Be nice to Frank.
He's not cheap. He's poor!

15:51.825 --> 15:54.244
[both laugh]

15:54.328 --> 15:58.165
I miss how we used
to shit on Frank together.

15:58.248 --> 15:59.833
[chuckles] It's so easy!

15:59.917 --> 16:03.379
[chuckles] Yeah, Louis,
you really know how to stick it to a guy.

16:04.296 --> 16:08.467
Uh, stick it to a guy
with your jokes, you know.

16:08.550 --> 16:11.303
Not with your, uh... your penis.

16:11.387 --> 16:13.806
-Hey, looks like it's going well.
-Too well.

16:13.889 --> 16:16.016
[Louis] Sue, thank you.

16:16.100 --> 16:20.479
It's such a blessing to spend
one last Thanksgiving with the old man.

16:20.562 --> 16:22.189
I want to tell him how much I'll miss him.

16:22.272 --> 16:24.733
[chuckles] Yeah, but don't.

16:26.026 --> 16:29.071
-[Stan and Louis laughing]
-I have to stop them from being so chummy.

16:29.154 --> 16:32.282
Twice now he's almost said something
that would blow the whole lie apart.

16:32.366 --> 16:36.620
Sue, just exactly how did you see
this whole thing playing out?

16:36.704 --> 16:37.538
I don't know!

16:37.621 --> 16:40.457
I was at a gay bar. I saw my old boss
getting his pickle sniffed.

16:40.541 --> 16:41.583
I had to think quick.

16:41.667 --> 16:46.005
You have to help me keep them distracted
until the neighbors get here for dessert.

16:47.047 --> 16:49.633
Honey, I wish I could, but what can I do?

16:49.717 --> 16:52.011
They're not gonna talk to me.
They hate me.

16:52.094 --> 16:54.304
[both laughing]

16:54.388 --> 16:58.308
Oh, Dad, these are the kind of things
I'm going to miss when you're--

16:58.392 --> 16:59.351
Dad!

17:02.521 --> 17:08.277
Uh, Frank just said
he's happy Nixon got a full pardon!

17:08.360 --> 17:10.571
-He said what?
-I said what?

17:13.824 --> 17:15.951
That's right, Stan. I'm ecstatic!

17:16.035 --> 17:19.413
I'll tell you, you know,
I wish he did a dozen Watergates!

17:19.496 --> 17:21.165
-What about accountability?
-How can you say that?

17:21.248 --> 17:23.292
Ah, fuck accountability!

17:23.375 --> 17:26.670
Christ, the Democrats should've had
better locks, and you know it, Stan!

17:26.754 --> 17:29.048
-Are you serious?
-He did some great things with China!

17:29.131 --> 17:31.675
-I've heard things in my day, but this...
-[Frank] Right over!

17:31.759 --> 17:34.178
-[no audible dialogue]
-♪ Now thank we all our God ♪

17:34.261 --> 17:37.473
♪ With hearts and hands and voices ♪

17:37.556 --> 17:40.601
♪ Who wondrous things has done ♪

17:40.684 --> 17:43.771
♪ In whom his world rejoices ♪

17:43.854 --> 17:46.315
♪ From our mothers' arms ♪

17:46.398 --> 17:48.817
♪ Has blessed us on our way ♪

17:48.901 --> 17:52.029
♪ With countless gifts of love ♪

17:52.112 --> 17:55.365
♪ And still is ours today ♪

17:58.410 --> 18:01.205
♪ O may this bounteous God ♪

18:01.288 --> 18:04.041
♪ Through all our life be near us ♪

18:04.124 --> 18:06.752
♪ With ever joyful hearts ♪

18:06.835 --> 18:09.797
♪ And blessed peace to cheer us ♪

18:09.880 --> 18:12.925
♪ To keep us in his grace ♪

18:13.008 --> 18:16.303
-♪ And guide us when perplexed... ♪
-[grunting]

18:16.386 --> 18:19.473
-So, are you gonna get me my money?
-I'll pay!

18:19.556 --> 18:21.683
I will! I will! I promise!

18:21.767 --> 18:23.352
I think he's had enough.

18:23.435 --> 18:25.062
Thank you so much.

18:28.357 --> 18:29.983
[indistinct chatter]

18:30.067 --> 18:34.488
Mrs. Bonfiglio, how have you been?

18:34.571 --> 18:35.614
Ah, wet!

18:35.697 --> 18:38.700
Whoa, guys, look! Buster's about to jump!

18:38.784 --> 18:40.994
How do you feel
on this Thanksgiving, Buster?

18:41.078 --> 18:44.498
Like the original Pilgrims did
all those years ago,

18:45.082 --> 18:49.002
ready to kick ass
with 400 pounds between my legs!

18:49.086 --> 18:51.588
-[Stan] Look who's here!
-[gasps]

18:51.672 --> 18:54.216
-Charlie Chaplins!
-[silent film piano music playing]

18:54.299 --> 18:56.885
-[indistinct chatter]
-My little tramps!

18:56.969 --> 19:00.514
-You haven't done this in years!
-[Stan scatting]

19:00.597 --> 19:01.849
[Otto gasps]

19:01.932 --> 19:03.559
[both chuckling]

19:03.642 --> 19:05.853
They cloned him!

19:05.936 --> 19:06.895
[plate shatters]

19:07.396 --> 19:10.232
Look at them together.
Why aren't you arguing right now?

19:10.315 --> 19:13.443
I'm sorry, but I ran out of nice things
to say about Nixon.

19:14.153 --> 19:16.530
I mean, I... I... I guess your dad
turned me a little.

19:17.281 --> 19:20.117
-[applause]
-[both laughing]

19:20.200 --> 19:23.120
-[indistinct chatter]
-[Louis] You still got it, Dad.

19:23.203 --> 19:27.040
Hey, kids, did you know
I once got a hole in one at Baltusrol?

19:27.124 --> 19:30.711
Kevin, I hear you've got a lady
in your life.

19:30.794 --> 19:33.672
She'd be in my life
if she picked up the stupid phone.

19:33.755 --> 19:37.426
I keep calling, but she stands
over the machine, mocking me.

19:37.509 --> 19:38.468
I can feel it!

19:38.552 --> 19:39.845
Oh dear.

19:39.928 --> 19:42.973
Young love can be so hard.

19:43.056 --> 19:45.893
I'll bet there's
a perfectly sensible reason

19:45.976 --> 19:48.187
why she's not answering the phone.

19:48.270 --> 19:50.147
What's that mean? You think
she got back together with Joel?

19:50.230 --> 19:53.192
I'm sure whoever this Joel is,

19:53.275 --> 19:55.777
he's not as handsome as you are.

19:55.861 --> 19:59.448
What are you talking about?
He's a man! He was bar mitzvahed!

19:59.531 --> 20:02.284
She... she's probably not
with anyone else.

20:02.367 --> 20:05.579
-You mean she's dead?
-I'm not saying she's dead.

20:05.662 --> 20:09.625
Then it's not too late to save her life!
I got to go find her. [groans] Alice.

20:09.708 --> 20:12.294
I didn't know
what Nguyen-Nguyen was gonna do.

20:12.377 --> 20:14.504
I just told her about a Columbo episode

20:14.588 --> 20:17.174
where a Vietnamese woman
poisoned her husband.

20:17.257 --> 20:18.842
Then I lent her some bleach.

20:18.926 --> 20:20.844
Yeah, you probably shouldn't repeat
that story.

20:20.928 --> 20:23.222
Well, thanks for the eggnog and the, uh...

20:24.806 --> 20:27.392
the memory loss, but I better get
Vic Junior to beddy-bye.

20:27.476 --> 20:29.978
Where is he anyway?
Did he, uh, leave without me?

20:30.062 --> 20:31.730
Oh, Jesus Christ.

20:31.813 --> 20:34.816
Evelyn, what have you done with that baby?

20:34.900 --> 20:38.737
I warned you! I don't want to move again!
I like these names!

20:38.820 --> 20:41.031
Here we are. I was changing him.

20:41.114 --> 20:43.158
Oh, right. [chuckles]

20:43.242 --> 20:44.868
I knew you were here all along

20:44.952 --> 20:48.247
and not dyeing your hair
and making a break for the state line.

20:48.330 --> 20:50.332
Okay. [chuckles]

20:50.415 --> 20:51.667
Good times. Better go.

20:51.750 --> 20:54.628
Please, just let me sniff my Geraldine
one more time.

20:54.711 --> 20:57.714
Don't touch my baby!

20:57.798 --> 21:00.050
Your woman is fucking weird, man!

21:00.133 --> 21:01.260
[screams]

21:01.343 --> 21:06.014
For God's sake, Evelyn, move on!
We're never gonna have a kid!

21:06.098 --> 21:08.225
You're the one who can't face the truth!

21:08.308 --> 21:10.727
It wasn't clams!

21:10.811 --> 21:14.064
And I'm starting to think
you lied about Frank's pants!

21:14.147 --> 21:18.485
I stole his pants
because they made me feel alive, Ev!

21:18.568 --> 21:20.237
In a way you never do!

21:20.320 --> 21:22.447
-You all have a Happy Easter. Okay.
-[giggling]

21:22.531 --> 21:24.116
You don't take me dancing!

21:24.199 --> 21:27.536
And you've never once watched me
shit in the woods!

21:27.619 --> 21:29.454
A man has needs!

21:29.538 --> 21:33.000
This neighborhood was way more normal
when I was on the goofies.

21:34.167 --> 21:36.378
[man] Buster Thunder Junior
is ready to jump!

21:36.461 --> 21:37.629
Here he goes!

21:37.713 --> 21:41.883
Sue, this was lovely,
but we should be on our way.

21:41.967 --> 21:45.178
It's a four-hour drive,
and I'd like to have your father awake

21:45.262 --> 21:46.763
at James Dean Curve.

21:46.847 --> 21:49.349
Oh, please don't go,
but here's your coats!

21:50.017 --> 21:51.935
Thank you, angel.

21:52.519 --> 21:54.438
And thank you, Frank.

21:54.521 --> 21:57.149
The turkey was... competently sliced.

21:57.232 --> 21:59.568
And I know how hard
that must've been for you to say.

22:00.402 --> 22:02.863
-Good to see you, son.
-You too, Dad.

22:02.946 --> 22:04.948
[man on TV]
Buster just might pull this off!

22:05.032 --> 22:09.411
-Let's all do this again next year!
-Sue, how could you be so insensitive?

22:09.494 --> 22:11.747
-What?
-[man] Uh-oh, he's picked up a wobble.

22:11.830 --> 22:15.334
Do this again next year?
Where? On Dad's grave?

22:15.417 --> 22:16.501
My what?

22:16.585 --> 22:19.504
Sue told me, Dad. Told me you're dying.

22:19.588 --> 22:22.549
-You told him I was dying?
-[man] Buster is airborne!

22:22.632 --> 22:23.717
Not in those words.

22:23.800 --> 22:25.635
Exactly in those words!

22:25.719 --> 22:28.680
[man] And he crashes
into the concrete riverbank!

22:28.764 --> 22:30.098
[all gasp]

22:30.182 --> 22:34.061
He came so close and then shit-a the bed!

22:34.144 --> 22:35.437
Why would you lie to me?

22:35.520 --> 22:37.356
I wanted you and Dad to make up!

22:37.439 --> 22:38.940
You thought so little of us

22:39.024 --> 22:42.486
that we couldn't make up
without you putting a tumor in his brain?

22:42.569 --> 22:44.529
You said you didn't give a shit about him!

22:44.613 --> 22:47.866
-Well, that's real nice!
-Oh, as nice as disowning me, Dad?

22:47.949 --> 22:49.326
[Stan] You disowned yourself

22:49.409 --> 22:52.245
the minute you decided
to lust over other men!

22:52.329 --> 22:55.749
It's not lust, Dad. It's love.
I'm a human being!

22:55.832 --> 22:57.626
I'm just the way God made me.

22:57.709 --> 23:01.505
There you go,
always blaming somebody else!

23:03.715 --> 23:05.050
Alice!

23:05.133 --> 23:06.927
Alice! Come out, please!

23:07.010 --> 23:09.888
I'm here to prove to you
I can give you your space!

23:11.139 --> 23:13.642
-Oh, Alice!
-Kevin, what are you doing here?

23:13.725 --> 23:16.061
Where the hell have you been, young lady?

23:16.144 --> 23:18.814
We had Thanksgiving at my aunt's house.

23:18.897 --> 23:20.440
You believe in Thanksgiving?

23:20.524 --> 23:22.651
[pants] I thought you were Jewish.

23:22.734 --> 23:25.487
[chuckles]

23:25.570 --> 23:28.740
This is a story
we're gonna tell our grandkids. [chuckles]

23:28.824 --> 23:30.117
You're creeping me out.

23:30.200 --> 23:32.786
Am I creeping you out
down there? [chuckles]

23:33.286 --> 23:36.373
-Hey, Alice, is this kid bothering you?
-Is this that fucking Joel?

23:36.456 --> 23:37.666
No, Kevin, this is--

23:37.749 --> 23:39.084
-[Mrs. Goldman] Oh my God!
-[Dr. Goldman] Daniel!

23:39.167 --> 23:40.085
My brother!

23:40.168 --> 23:41.545
Ow, shit, my hand!

23:41.628 --> 23:42.963
You knocked out my tooth!

23:43.046 --> 23:44.840
[splutters] You can have one of mine.

23:44.923 --> 23:46.842
Kevin, get out of here!

23:46.925 --> 23:48.844
I never want to see you again!

23:48.927 --> 23:50.595
But it's Thanksgiving!

23:50.679 --> 23:53.723
[Louis] You have no idea
what it's like being your son!

23:53.807 --> 23:56.893
You have no idea
what it's like being your father!

23:56.977 --> 24:01.606
I had to bail you out of jail
for defiling that Greyhound station!

24:01.690 --> 24:04.526
Bus travel has lost all its class.

24:04.609 --> 24:05.610
Dad, stop!

24:05.694 --> 24:08.947
You shame Louis, but maybe
if his lifestyle was more accepted,

24:09.030 --> 24:11.533
he wouldn't have to do those things
in secret at the bus station.

24:11.616 --> 24:14.369
-Oh, Sue, I'd still go to the bus station.
-See?

24:14.453 --> 24:16.496
-The man's a deviant.
-And you're a bigot!

24:16.580 --> 24:19.374
Stan, come on. It's Thanksgiving.

24:19.458 --> 24:21.084
Louis is a good guy.

24:21.168 --> 24:23.587
Yeah, he's got a little sugar in his tank,
but you know...

24:23.670 --> 24:27.466
Sugar in the tank?
I could kick your ass across this room.

24:27.549 --> 24:30.135
-I was sticking up for you!
-Stay out of this.

24:30.218 --> 24:33.138
Like you should've stayed out
of my daughter 15 years ago.

24:33.221 --> 24:34.639
-Dad!
-He's right.

24:34.723 --> 24:38.768
Dad and I got along great until the day
you married this balding piece of shit.

24:38.852 --> 24:42.606
Eh, you know what?
You two can just go fuck off!

24:42.689 --> 24:45.650
Jesus Christ,
this woman worked herself to the bone

24:45.734 --> 24:47.319
to make this perfect day for you.

24:47.402 --> 24:50.030
And she asked me to help. Did I complain?

24:50.113 --> 24:51.698
A little at first.

24:51.781 --> 24:54.951
But then, I cut short
a very, very happy nap,

24:55.035 --> 24:56.244
one of those good ones

24:56.328 --> 24:58.914
where you're sleeping so peacefully
you feel like you're dead,

24:58.997 --> 25:00.874
you know, and you're thinking,
"Oh my God, it's finally over,"

25:00.957 --> 25:03.627
right, to drive my snotty kids
to the grocery store

25:03.710 --> 25:06.087
to get the fancy cranberries that I hate,

25:06.171 --> 25:08.423
just to help her
bring you two back together.

25:08.507 --> 25:09.841
And now I'm the bad guy?

25:09.925 --> 25:12.177
Well, fuck you and your fighting!

25:12.260 --> 25:14.012
Jesus Christ,
why don't you count your blessings?

25:14.095 --> 25:15.972
You're lucky your old man's still alive.

25:16.056 --> 25:18.850
Christ, what I wouldn't give
to hear my dad call me a "whiny bitch"

25:18.934 --> 25:20.018
just one more time!

25:20.101 --> 25:22.646
I'm happy to fill in, shit-bird!

25:22.729 --> 25:25.982
Oh, no, no, no,
I said "whiny bitch," you fuck!

25:26.066 --> 25:28.527
So fuck you, Stan! And fuck you, Louis!

25:28.610 --> 25:32.239
And, Marilyn, I really enjoyed
the story about the ducks.

25:32.322 --> 25:34.282
I hope that law passes
so the state doesn't kill 'em.

25:34.366 --> 25:36.451
-Aw.
-But fuck you!

25:36.535 --> 25:39.287
[groaning]

25:39.371 --> 25:41.081
[sad music playing]

25:45.168 --> 25:46.002
Ah!

25:46.086 --> 25:47.212
[tires squeal]

25:55.720 --> 25:57.973
[sobs]

25:58.056 --> 25:59.516
[babbling]

25:59.599 --> 26:02.102
Oh, you like Grandpa Bill's keys.

26:02.185 --> 26:03.937
Yeah.

26:04.020 --> 26:09.359
He was a miserable son of a bitch,
but his keys go jingle-jangle-jingle.

26:09.442 --> 26:11.444
[Sue chewing voraciously]

26:13.863 --> 26:15.282
-Hey, Sue.
-[baby laughs]

26:15.365 --> 26:17.867
Look, I'm sorry
that today went so badly for you.

26:17.951 --> 26:19.077
I can't talk now.

26:20.370 --> 26:21.955
I didn't eat anything all day.

26:22.038 --> 26:23.915
Hey, remember how you said
I was too obsessed

26:23.999 --> 26:27.627
with figuring out what my dad meant
when he said "box 16"?

26:27.711 --> 26:31.756
Well, I think this thing with Louis
is your version of that.

26:31.840 --> 26:34.676
And it's not good for you either. [scoffs]

26:34.759 --> 26:36.636
We're never gonna get what we want.

26:36.720 --> 26:38.096
You're right.

26:38.179 --> 26:39.848
I'm gonna go wolf down some cobbler

26:39.931 --> 26:43.351
and then pass out in the bathtub
with this thermos of mulled wine.

26:43.977 --> 26:45.562
You're on Megan duty.

26:47.939 --> 26:49.024
[laughing]

26:49.107 --> 26:50.984
Guess what, Megan?

26:51.067 --> 26:53.445
We never have to see Pop-Pop again

26:53.528 --> 26:55.488
'cause Mommy was nutty today.

26:55.572 --> 26:57.365
Yes, she was.

26:57.449 --> 26:59.451
[laughing] Ah!

27:00.577 --> 27:02.912
[Frank] Oh, you like that little one, huh?

27:05.332 --> 27:07.917
Oh my God. Sixteen.

27:10.378 --> 27:12.797
So much to be thankful for.

27:12.881 --> 27:14.507
-[baby babbling]
-[thud]

27:14.591 --> 27:15.925
Holy shit!

27:16.009 --> 27:18.887
-[Sue] You okay down there?
-Everyone's alive, honey bear!

27:18.970 --> 27:20.263
Keep drinking!

27:20.930 --> 27:23.892
